gomodel:SYNGO_2814  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Wnt7a acts through Dvl1 to regulate spine morphogenesis\"\nFig.3: \"Wnt mutant mice exhibit defects in dendritic spine morphogenesis and excitatory synaptic function in the hippocampus\"\nFig.4: \"Postsynaptic expression of Dvl1 induces spine maturation and enhances excitatory synaptic function\"\nFig.5: \"Postsynaptic expression of Dvl1 increases excitatory input onto spines\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal slices were prepared as described (1) from postnatal day (P)8 wild-type or Wnt7a; Dvl1 mutant mice\"\n- \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 Sprague-Dawley rat e...\"" ;
